public class Main {
  public static void main(String[] args) {
    // display the prime numbers between 1 and 500
    System.out.println("Prime numbers between 1 and 500:");
    for (int i = 1; i <= 500; i++) {
      if (isPrime(i)) {
        System.out.print(i + " ");
      }
    }
    System.out.println();
  }

  public static boolean isPrime(int n) {
    if (n < 2) {
      return false;
    }
    for (int i = 2; i <= Math.sqrt(n); i++) {
      if (n % i == 0) {
        return false;
      }
    }
    return true;
  }
}
The isPrime() method first checks if the number is less than 2, and returns false if it is, because 0 and 1 are not considered prime numbers. If the number is greater than or equal to 2, the method checks if it is divisible by any integer between 2 and the square root of the number. If the number is divisible by any of these integers, the method returns false; otherwise, it returns true.
